TODO17 retriable failed-to-send retry fix evidence summary

Implementation:
- packages/coding-agent/src/core/extensions/builtin/mcp/health.ts now exposes withMcpRetriableFailedSendRetry(), which calls isRetriableMcpError in production, excludes session-expiry errors handled by the existing session wrapper, marks the connection degraded, renews once, retries once, and surfaces the retry error without looping.
- packages/coding-agent/src/core/extensions/builtin/mcp/expose/register.ts wraps only the client.callTool send in withMcpRetriableFailedSendRetry(), leaving pre-call ping/renew establishment bounded by existing health semantics.
- packages/coding-agent/test/mcp/reconnect.test.ts adds real-fixture regressions for successful failed-to-send retry and retry failure without looping, while keeping the existing in-flight no-duplicate test.

