Static/slop audit:
- Artifact: .omo/evidence/task-17-retry-fix-static-audit.log
- Observable: no as any, ts-ignore/expect-error, inline import(), enum/namespace/module, infinite retry loop, or real-token/private-key markers in changed tracked files/evidence; authorization fields redacted as <mock-redacted>.

Adversarial classes:
- stale_state: retry uses entry.connection.current client after connection.renew(), and QA spawnCounter=2 plus fixturePayloadSeen proves the retried call used the renewed server, not the stale disposed client.
- dirty_worktree: unrelated untracked .omo/evidence/*stop-hook* and todo17 gate-review files existed before work and were left untouched/uncommitted.
- misleading_success_output: evidence uses payload, model request, send-attempt log, spawn counter, and server call counter, not pass counts only.
- flaky_tests/timing-sensitive: tests use deterministic injected send failures and existing fixture counters; no blind sleeps added.
- hung_or_long_commands: QA run is bounded by runCli timeout; cleanup receipt proves sandbox removal and fixture pids dead; reconnect timers remain safe/unref through existing code.
- malformed_input: /mcp reconnect command handling was not touched; impacted commands.test.ts passed.
- cancel/resume: tool abort/cancel semantics were not changed; impacted register-call.test.ts passed.
- repeated_interruptions: in-flight crash negative remains covered by unit test and manual QA, both showing callCounter=1.
- prompt_injection: fixture/server error text is treated as model-visible data only; no command execution from server-provided text.

Conclusion: TODO17 gate blocker fixed and proven for exactly one post-reconnect retry of a retriable failed-to-send MCP call, while preserving no auto-retry for in-flight transport death.
